{
  "texts": [
    "We refer the reader to the work of Fern ˊandez-Castilla et al. (2019) for a more detailed explanation of cross-classified random effects.",
    "Further, several modeling recommendations for es-timating outcome-specific effects in meta-analyses with dependent effect size data have been formulated by Fern ˊandez-Castilla et al. (2021), and there is one that we like to highlight here.",
    "The three-level model that we illustrated in our tutorial (Assink & Wibbelink, 2016) is often used to estimate a mean effect size for specific outcomes next to an overall effect size.",
    "For instance, Spruit et al. (2016) synthesized primary studies examining the effects of physical activity interventions on internalizing behaviors in adolescents using the three-level model.",
    "Their aim was to obtain one overall intervention effect as well as several outcomespecific effects for types of internalizing behaviors (i.e., depression, anxiety, and \"other\" internalizing problems)."
  ]
}